</div>
<div id="ftn2">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref2" name="_ftn2"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[2]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE"> Incarnation = l’acte par lequel Dieu se fait chair, le Verbe se fait homme. </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn3">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref3" name="_ftn3"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[3]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span>, <i>Allocution à Capoue</i>, 24 mai 1992, § 9, in Actae Apostolicae 85, (1993), 2, p.668</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn4">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref4" name="_ftn4"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[4]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> Cf. Maria Giovanna <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Muzj,</span> <i>Il linguaggio catechetico dell’iconografia mariana</i>, in Aa Vv, <i>Il posto di Mara nella nuova evangelizzazione</i>, (E. Toniolo ed.), p. 206-233 ; Lire aussi le commentaire de la Vierge de tendresse par Pavel <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Evdokimov</span>, in T. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Spidlik, G. Guaita, M. Campatelli,</span> <i>Testi mariani del secondo Millennio, </i>II, Città nuova, 2000, p. 482-483</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn5">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref5" name="_ftn5"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[5]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> J<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">. Bernard</span>, <i>Torah et culte chez les Rabbins, confessions divergentes,</i> dans Mélanges de science Religieuse, Lille, Janvier-mars 1997 pp. 38-71.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn6">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref6" name="_ftn6"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[6]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Pour approfondir ces points, nous conseillons au lecteur l’exemple de la spiritualité montfortaine dont l’enracinement biblique est particulièrement fort. Cf. F. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Breynaert</span>, <i>L’arbre de vie, symbole central de la spiritualité de saint Louis-Marie de Montfort,</i> Parole et silence, Paris 2006.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn7">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref7" name="_ftn7"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[7]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Dans la ligne de l’analyse narrative, on parlera d’analyse sémiotique.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn8">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref8" name="_ftn8"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[8]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Mais le Coran ne transmet pas de réponse de Marie, le récit de l’Annonciation n’y est pas un récit d’Alliance : il est question d’un décret irrévocable de la part de Dieu (Coran, sourate 3, 45-49 et 19, 17b-21)        </p>
</div>
<div id="ftn9">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref9" name="_ftn9"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[9]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span lang="FR-BE">Exode Rabba., 42,9</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn10">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref10" name="_ftn10"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[10]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Philon d’Alexandrie, <i>De decalogo,</i>32</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn11">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref11" name="_ftn11"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[11]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span><span lang="FR-BE">, <i>Lettre apostolique « Mulieris dignitatem »</i> (15 août 1988)</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn12">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref12" name="_ftn12"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[12]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span>, <i>Lettre apostolique « Redemptoris Custos » </i>§ 32 (15 août 1989)</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn13">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref13" name="_ftn13"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[13]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> J. BERNARD, <i>Genèse 1-3 :</i> <i>Lecture et traditions de lectures,</i> dans Mélanges de science religieuse (1984), n°3-4, p. 109-128 ; (1986) Ibid., n°1, p. 3-55.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn14">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref14" name="_ftn14"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[14]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> C’est pourquoi le commandement donné au jardin de la Genèse est à comprendre dans le sens des commandements contemporains à la première rédaction de Genèse 2-3, notamment l’interdiction de l’occultisme et de la magie, l’interdiction de l’inceste et des crimes (Exode 20, 22 et suivants). Ce commandement est ensuite à mettre en parallèle avec toute la Torah (écrite et orale) donnée au Sinaï.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn15">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref15" name="_ftn15"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[15]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase;">Philon</span><span lang="FR-BE">, <i>Du Décalogue</i> 10.45</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn16">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref16" name="_ftn16"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[16]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Attribuée à Rabbi Siméon ben Jochai († 150 environ après J-C) cf. Cantique Rabba 4,7.1</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn17">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref17" name="_ftn17"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[17]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Tradition de la synagogue écrite entre 500 et 750 après J-C.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn18">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref18" name="_ftn18"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[18]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Shabbat 145b-146a ; Yebamoth 103b (Rabbi Yochanan † 279, qui semble se faire le porte parole de Rabbi Siméon ben Yochai, vers 150)</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn19">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref19" name="_ftn19"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[19]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Au passage, nous voyons comment la méthode « narrative », la méthode « canonique », et l’« Approche par le recours aux traditions juives d’interprétation » sont complémentaires pour éclairer l’interprétation de la Bible. <span lang="FR-BE">Cf. </span><span style="mso-bidi-font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'GDDEZZ+Palatino-Bold','serif';">COMMISSION BIBLIQUE PONTIFICALE,</span><i><span style="mso-bidi-font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'CenturyOldStyle-Bold','serif';"> L’interprétation de la Bible dans l’Église, </span></i><span style="mso-bidi-font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'CenturyOldStyle-Bold','serif';">Vatican 1993.</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn20">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref20" name="_ftn20"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[20]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> Ignazio<span style="text-transform: uppercase;"> Calabuig</span>, <i>Il culto di Maria in occidente,</i> In Pontificio Istituto Liturgico sant’Anselmo. Scientia Liturgica, sotto la direzione di A.J. CHUPUNGCO, vol V, Piemme 1998. p. 307-310</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn21">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref21" name="_ftn21"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[21]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Texte latin dans : (a cura di) J. JANINI, Liber missarum de Toledo y libros misticos, Toledo 1982, p. 6-7</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn22">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref22" name="_ftn22"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[22]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Extrait de la Bénédiction solennelle du jour de Noël, Missel Romain 88</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn23">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref23" name="_ftn23"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[23]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Antienne d’ouverture de la messe votive 2 « La vierge Marie à l’Annonciation du Seigneur », <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Congrégation du Culte Divin, </span><i>Messes en l’honneur de la Vierge Marie</i>, Desclée Mame, p. 37</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn24">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref24" name="_ftn24"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[24]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>La fête du 2 février reçut des appellations variées : Le 40<sup>e</sup> jour ; La fête de la rencontre, « Hypapante » ; La fête de saint Syméon ; La Présentation du Seigneur (Eglise romaine actuelle) ; L’entrée du Seigneur au temple (Eglise syrienne) ; La purification de Marie au temple. (Déjà dans la tradition Gélasienne et dans la liturgie romaine jusqu’en 1969).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn25">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref25" name="_ftn25"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[25]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Antienne pour la fête du 2 février, <i>Missel sextuplex,</i> 7<sup>ème</sup> siècle, traduction F. Breynaert.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn26">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref26" name="_ftn26"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[26]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Le Christ était caché dans les cieux, il a été « révélé » quand il est venu sur la terre, dans le sein virginal de Marie. <span lang="FR-BE">« </span>Le sacrement de notre salut », c’est le Christ.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn27">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref27" name="_ftn27"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[27]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Le Christ accompli la promesse faite à David (Lc 1, 78-79).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn28">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref28" name="_ftn28"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[28]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Le texte cite le cantique de Zacharie (Lc 1,78) : Dieu visite son peuple.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn29">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref29" name="_ftn29"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[29]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>Dans la parole « Béni soit celui qui vient au nom du Seigneur », on reconnaît l’acclamation de la foule à Jérusalem. Mais avant la venue à Jérusalem, il y a sa venue dans l’Incarnation.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               Et dans la parole « Qui comme un époux sort de sa tente et il nous illumine » c’est le psaume 18,6 cité pour dire que le Christ est l’Epoux : l’Incarnation signifie que Dieu épouse l’humanité.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn30">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref30" name="_ftn30"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[30]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE"> Liturgie de Noël, </span>Sacramentaire Veronese, §1247 - remontant selon toute probabilité au pontificat de Gélase I (492-496)</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn31">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref31" name="_ftn31"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[31]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> Cf. Ignazio CALABUIG, <i>Los formularios V-IX de la secciòn XL del sacramentarlo de Verona,</i> Roma, 1964</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn32">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref32" name="_ftn32"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[32]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE"> La richesse des notes montre comment le Vatican II puise dans les siècles qui l’ont précédé. </span><span lang="EN-GB">(5) Cf. S Germain Cont. Hom. in Annunt. </span><span lang="IT">Deiparae: PG 98, 328 A; In Dorm 2: col. 357. </span>Anastasius Antioc. Serm. 2 de de Annunt.2: PG 89, 1377 serm. <span lang="EN-GB">3,2 col. 1388 C S Andreas Cret.Can. in B.V. Nat. 1, col. 812 A ; Hom. in dorm. 1: col. 1068 C S Sophronius, or. 2 in in Annunt, 18: PG 87 (3) 3237 BD. (6) S Irénée, Adv. Haer. III 22,4: PG 7,959 A; Harvey 2, 123. (7) " ibbidem ; Harvey 2, 124. (8) S Epiphanus, Haer 78, 18: PG 42, 728 CD 729 (9) S Hieronymus, Epis. 22, 21: PL 22, 408. Cf. S Augustin, sermo 51, 2, 3,: PL 38, 335: serm. </span><span lang="IT">232, 2 col. col. 1108. S Cyrillus Hieros, catec. </span><span lang="EN-GB">12,15 PG 33, 741 S.Jean Chrisosthome, in Ps 44,7 PG 55, 193. </span><span lang="IT">S Damascène, Hom. 2 in in dorm. B.M.V. 3: PG 96, 728.</span></p>
</div>
