</div>
<div id="ftn64">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref64" name="_ftn64"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[64]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Irénée de Lyon</span>, <i>Contres les hérésies III,19,1</i></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn65">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref65" name="_ftn65"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[65]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Irénée de Lyon</span>, <i>Contres les hérésies IV 33, 11</i></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn66">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref66" name="_ftn66"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[66]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> Cf. S.-M. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Cecchin</span>, <i>Maria Signora Santa e Immacolata nel pensiero francescano,</i> PAMI, Città del Vaticano 2001, p. 7-9</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn67">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref67" name="_ftn67"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[67]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="EN-GB"> Saint <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Bonaventure, </span>«Thesaurus » (Opera Omnia V), cap. </span><span lang="FR-BE">VIII. </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn68">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref68" name="_ftn68"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[68]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span lang="EN-GB" style="text-transform: uppercase; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB;">Vatican II</span> reprend cette vision : juste après avoir évoqué le dessein de Dieu (LG 52), il est question du « <i>lien étroit et indissoluble</i> » qui unit Marie et son Fils (LG 53)</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn69">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref69" name="_ftn69"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[69]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE"> Ce que reprend <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Paul VI</span>, Lettre apostolique “<i>Marialis cultus</i>” § 7.</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn70">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref70" name="_ftn70"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[70]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> «Similis Christo Maria in praedestinatione. Similis, in quam, in praedestinatione, quondam Christus praedestinatus est non ut Deus, sed ut homo filius Mariae, ergo una cum Cristo predestinata est Maria» (Laurent de Brindisi, Sermon V in Concepitone Immacolata, Mariale [Padova 1928] 454). </span><span lang="FR-BE">Saint Laurent de Brindisi (†1629), capucin, est docteur de l’Eglise.</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn71">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref71" name="_ftn71"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[71]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Saint <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">François d’Assise</span>, <i>Lettre aux fidèles</i> II, 5 dans <i>Ecrits,</i> Sources chrétiennes 285, Cerf, Paris 1981, p. 232</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn72">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref72" name="_ftn72"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[72]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> Cf. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Francesco</span></span><!-- [if supportFields]><span
style='text-transform:uppercase'><span style='mso-element:field-begin'></span></span><span
lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'> XE &quot;<span style='text-transform:
uppercase'>Francesco</span>&quot; </span><![endif]--><!-- [if supportFields]><span
style='text-transform:uppercase'><span style='mso-element:field-end'></span></span><![endif]--><span lang="IT">, <i>Ultima voluntas sanctae Clarae scripta</i>, 1.</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn73">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref73" name="_ftn73"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[73]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Nicolas Cabasilas est né à Thessalonique entre 1319 et 1323, il mourut aux alentours de 1398. Neveu du patriarche Nilo Cabasilas, Nicolas Cabasilas est un des plus célèbres auteurs du XIV° siècle dans l’Eglise Byzantine. Il eut des engagements politiques et ne se fit pas moine mais il défendit son ami Grégoire Palamas avec lequel il demeura au mont Athos pendant un an, il fut aussi ami de Demetrio Cidone qui traduisit en grec la somme de saint Thomas d’Aquin. Il concilia l’ascèse avec une haute culture et montra que la spiritualité pouvait être vécue en dehors des monastères. <span lang="EN-GB">Cf. </span><a href="http://www.culturamariana.com/"><span lang="EN-GB">www.culturamariana.com</span></a></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn74">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref74" name="_ftn74"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[74]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase; mso-ansi-language: FR-BE;">N.Cabasilas</span>, <i>Homélie de sur la Nativité</i>, dans G. LIMOURIS, <i>Les homélies mariales de Nicolas Cabasilas, monument liturgique et théologique,</i> dans <i>La mère de Jésus-Christ et la communion des saints dans la liturgie,</i> conférences saint-Serge, 32<sup>ème</sup> semaine d’Etude liturgiques, Paris 25-28 juin 1985, Rome 1986, p. 149-171.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn75">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref75" name="_ftn75"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[75]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Nicolas Cabasilas n’a pas exactement la doctrine du péché originel et de l’Immaculée conception que l’Eglise latine développera de son côté. Pour lui, le péché n’est pas transmis. Tous sont égaux. Marie n’a pas une grâce de plus que les autres.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn76">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref76" name="_ftn76"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[76]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> N<span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase; mso-ansi-language: FR-BE;">. Cabasilas</span>, <i>Homélie de la Nativité</i>, op. cit.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn77">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref77" name="_ftn77"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[77]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Marie n’est pas conditionnée ni privée de liberté, mais simplement Dieu a un but lorsqu’il a voulu son existence - comme pour chacun de nous.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn78">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref78" name="_ftn78"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[78]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Vatican II a donné pour titre au chapitre 8 de Lumen Gentium : « De la Bienheureuse Marie, Vierge, Mère de Dieu, <i>dans le mystère du Christ et de l’Eglise</i> ».</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn79">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref79" name="_ftn79"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[79]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span>, Audience du 8 mai 1996.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn80">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref80" name="_ftn80"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[80]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span lang="IT" style="text-transform: uppercase;">L. Gambero</span><span lang="IT">, <i>Maria nel pensiero dei teologi latini medievali,</i> San Paolo 2000, p. 305-306</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn81">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref81" name="_ftn81"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[81]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Duns Scot, En III sententiarum, d 3, q 1</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn82">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref82" name="_ftn82"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[82]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;">Jean Paul II, audience 1° mai 1996</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn83">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref83" name="_ftn83"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[83]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Card. J. Ratzinger, La fille de Sion, édition Parole et Silence 2002, p.79</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn84">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref84" name="_ftn84"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[84]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> Nous allons suivre A.SERRA, “<i>Immacolata”</i>, in <i>Nuovo dizionario di mariologia</i>, a cura di de Fiores, ed. san Paolo, Milano 1985, p.691-695</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn85">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref85" name="_ftn85"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[85]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Targum = Traduction expliquée de la Bible, au temps du retour de l’exil, vers 400 avant J-C.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn86">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref86" name="_ftn86"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[86]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Targum du psaume 68</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn87">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref87" name="_ftn87"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[87]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Pavel <span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase; mso-ansi-language: FR-BE;">Evdokimov</span> (1901-1970), <i>La femme et la salut du monde. Étude d’anthropologie chrétienne sur les charismes de la femme,</i> Tournai-Paris 1958, p. 217-218.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn88">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref88" name="_ftn88"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[88]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Nous l’apprenons par Egesippe, originaire d’Orient, probablement de la Palestine, écrivit ses "mémoires" vers 150-200. De la compilation d’Egesippe différents extraits nous sont parvenus par Eusèbe de Césarée. Eusèbe, sur l’autorité d’Egesippe, affirme que Cléophas était un frère de saint Joseph.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn89">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref89" name="_ftn89"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[89]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> S. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">De Fiores</span>, articolo <i>Vergine</i>, nel <i>Nuovo dizionario di mariologia,</i> a cura di de Fiores, ed. san Paolo 1985, p.1317-1322</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn90">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref90" name="_ftn90"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[90]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> R. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Laurentin</span>, <i>Les évangiles de l’enfance du Christ,</i> Desclée et DDB, Parigi 1982, p.475-476.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn91">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref91" name="_ftn91"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[91]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Y<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">.-M. Blanchard, « </span>Né d’un vouloir de chair ? La conception virginale au regard du 4<sup>ème</sup> évangile », dans Aa Vv, <i>La virginité de Marie,</i> Mediaspaul, Paris 1998, pp.25-31, p. 27. <span lang="IT">Comparer avec PERRELLA S.M., <i>Maria, vergine e madre, la verginità feconda di Maria tra fede, storia e teologia,</i> San Paolo, Milano 2003, p. 100-107</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn92">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref92" name="_ftn92"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[92]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Sauf si ces textes des pères ont eux-mêmes été retouchés, ce qui est difficile à savoir puisque nous n’en avons que des manuscrits tardifs. Mais il serait étonnant que tous ces auteurs, dans tant de régions, aient tous été retouchés.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn93">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref93" name="_ftn93"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[93]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Une discussion à ce propos est toujours possible (cf. La note précédente).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn94">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref94" name="_ftn94"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[94]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Tertullianus,</span> <i>De Carne Christi</i> 19,1-2 et 20, 3-7.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn95">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref95" name="_ftn95"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[95]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Il n’y a donc vraiment pas de raison d’éliminer l’hypothèse d’une version biblique au singulier concernant Jésus sous prétexte qu’elle serait « docète » comme le fait Y.-M. Blanchard, op. cit.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn96">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref96" name="_ftn96"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[96]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> Matthieu parle d’un ange qui roule la pierre, quand Jésus est déjà ressuscité et que le tombeau est vide, Jésus est sorti en laissant intacte cette pierre…</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn97">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="file:///D:/Users/FRANCOISE/Documents/EDITIONS/livres/A%20l'%C3%A9coute%20de%20Marie/Ecoute%20de%20Marie%20partie%201.docx#_ftnref97" name="_ftn97"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[97]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="DE"> H. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Asmussen</span>, <i>Maria die Mutter Gottes.</i> Evangelisches Verlag, Stoccarda 1951, p.19</span></p>
